        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=77008&amp;TOPIC_ID=8963&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Do+we+want+to+be+a+pet+class+%3F&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Well, i think i speak for alot of the people who play this game causually, when i say that pets are the sole reason i play a necromancer.  Soloing is the only way I can really play the game, i often don't have more than 2 hours at a time when i can play.  When I say soloing, i don't mean experience grinding my way to 60, cause sure root/dot is fine for that, but I mean PLAYING the game by myself.  Playing the game means going and seeing things, exploring dungeons, doing quests, camping items, vending, etc.  And the one thing I do know is i certainly wouldn't be able to do 90 percent of the things I can now if we didn't have the pet we do.  MAges and Beastlords may have better pets, shaman may be better at killing some things, but none of them have the tools to make spelunking possible.  Shadowknights are close to us, but its our pet that makes us superior to them, and if you don't think so, ask them to solo the lguk king room at 54.</P><P>The efficiency of pets are what make us the great class we are.  Sure, i'm only level 55, but i've gotten to explore alot of the world, killed alot of mobs I shouldn't have been able to if it weren't for ole jabober.  I feel sorry for the pathetic druid/wizard types who can at best explore a dungeon invis, i get to kill most of the mobs in that dungeon thanks to pet, then kill some more.  Sure we don't have the unbalanced pet we once did, but we are still a one man group.  </P><P>If they took away all our DOT's, we'd still be a functional class; if they took away our pet, we'd be limited to grouping or killing purely for experience. <BR>Granted that none of this applies to POP, since that high end game is all geared toward raid type stuff, only time will tell.  The only thing I know for certain about EQ (aside from every other word out of verants mouth is a lie) is that what other people claim isn't possible usually is, and we may just find people soloing thier way to 65.</P><P>CAVEAT- don't take this to mean I agree with the crap they are pulling in POP.  We should be the masters of DOT, no question.  Shaman get great heals AND slow, Druids get same heals and Nukes, we need top DOTs to remain competative.</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
